                <h2>1. Colosseum: The Eternal Arena of Gladiators</h2>
                <p>The Colosseum is also that prime number in the catalogue of landmarks that endures as a testament to Rome’s grand history in the world.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Its function was mainly to hold gladiatorial combats, public spectacles, and even staged naval combats. This marvel of architecture, as most would say, could accommodate above 50,000 people and is an example of Roman ingenuity in shipping.</li>
